headline: Airbnb Stock (ABNB) Teeters Like a House of Cards as U.S. Travel Slumps
summary: Airbnb’s (ABNB) lackluster stock performance isn’t anything new for investors who’ve been following it for a while. This year alone, it’s down nearly 8%. Over the last 12 months, it’s down 22%, and in the past five years, the company has lost around 13% of its value. Late last week, Airbnb reported disappointing Q1 results with accompanying weak guidance for Q2.
